# --- UltraMemory harness (managed) ---
# Placement Contract: if your CLAUDE.md has a numbered hard-rules section with a `0.x` band, add
# this as the next free `0.x` right above RULE 1; if it has numbered rules but no `0.x` band,
# create the band and place this as RULE 0.7; if it has no hard-rules section, create one high in
# the file and make this its first entry. NEVER renumber existing rules (keeps "Rule N" citations
# valid). The installer inserts this block verbatim; `uninstall` removes everything between the
# two sentinel lines and nothing else.

**RULE 0.7 — Multi-file builds ride the harness. No unbound fan-out, no "done" without a green gate.**
> Any task that implements a multi-item plan or changes 2+ files MUST run through the harness, not
> ad-hoc edits or unbound subagents. (1) GROUND a machine-readable atomic checklist — verify every
> path, literal, schema, and endpoint against real source, never from memory. (2) STOP for explicit
> human approval of the checklist AND the gate command before building — "more autonomous" applies
> to execution, never to the decision to start. (3) EXECUTE via the `checklist-bound-execution`
> skill: it arms the `.claude/.harness-active` Stop gate, binds every spawned worker to its
> checklist item VERBATIM, and re-checks each item with a read-only adversarial verifier and bounded
> loop-back. Never fan work out to subagents or a Workflow without binding each to a verbatim
> checklist item. An item is done ONLY when its verifier verdict is pass:true AND the global gate
> (build / lint / tests) is green. Skip the harness for trivial single-file edits, pure Q&A, and
> read-only investigation.

**Recall first — actively, not just passively.**
> UltraMemory recall-first hook injects prompt-relevant memory before each turn, but that is PASSIVE
> and prompt-scoped. For anything the project should already know (a URL, a prior decision, where a
> credential lives, whether we have done X, what the fix was last time) ACTIVELY call the
> `memory_recall` or `search` tool FIRST; never answer from working memory or say
> I-do-not-have-it / not-grounded-this-session without recalling. Persist durable facts and decisions
> with `memory_write`. Pair with current library/API docs (Context7) and current external facts
> (Exa) — that trio is the trifecta. The hook and this active-recall rule work TOGETHER; do not pick
> one.
